The paper proposes a temporal knowledge graph embedding model that incorporates time information into entity/relation representations. This involves the use of additive time series decomposition and mapping of representations into the space of multi-dimensional Gaussian distributions. The model achieves state-of-the-art performance on link prediction over temporal KGs and can predict the occurrence time of facts with missing time annotations, as well as the existence of future events. Based on these aspects, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.LG (machine learning), and cs.DB (databases). The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as word embeddings, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CL (computation and language) and cs.IR (information retrieval) sub-categories.
